LOCATION:Newman Auditorium (Emeritus Hall) - Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:The Sierra Ensemble - SRJC's Chamber Concert Series
DESCRIPTION:This violin\, French horn and piano trio has performed throug
 hout the United States and the world since the late 90s. Rich in flavor\,
  the trio brings to the stage a repertoire that adds depth to the violin\
 , horn and piano through commissions and associations with other artists.
   The ensemble was awarded grants for two residency programs in Turkey an
 d was the resident chamber ensemble at the Pera College of Music in Istan
 bul.  To help expand the horn trio repertoire\, past engagements have inc
 luded commissioning composers Russell Steinberg and Tolga Ozdemir\; recen
 t commissions include new works by Andres Carrizo and Aida Shirazi\, and 
 Jan Bevan\, poet and author.  Janis Lieberman\, horn\; Matthew Vincent\, 
 violin\; and Marc Steiner\, piano.  &#160\;  Program:  Charles Koechlin\,
  Quatre Petites Pieces for Violin\, Horn and Piano  Richard Aldag\, Trio 
 for Violin\, Horn and Piano  Florence Price\, Fantasy No. 1 in G minor fo
 r Violin and Piano  Lev Kogan\, Kaddish for Horn Solo  Elsa Barraine\, Cr
 ├®puscules for Horn and Piano  Johannes Brahms\, Trio in Eb Major\; Opus 
 40 for Piano\, Violin and Horn  &#160\;  Ticket Prices:  Season tickets (
 all 6 concerts): $155  Mini Season (any 3 concerts): $90  Individual tick
 ets: $35  Student tickets (with valid ID): $20  &#160\;Buy tickets here! 
 (https://www.cityboxoffice.com/?category=36)  SRJC Chamber Concerts Websi
 te: https://chamberconcerts.santarosa.edu/ (https://chamberconcerts.santa
 rosa.edu/)&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This violin\, French horn and piano tri
 o has performed throughout the United States and the world since the late
  90s. Rich in flavor\, the trio brings to the stage a repertoire that add
 s depth to the violin\, horn and piano through commissions and associatio
 ns with other artists.</p><p>  The ensemble was awarded grants for two re
 sidency programs in Turkey and was the resident chamber ensemble at the P
 era College of Music in Istanbul.</p><p>  To help expand the horn trio re
 pertoire\, past engagements have included commissioning composers Russell
  Steinberg and Tolga Ozdemir\; recent commissions include new works by An
 dres Carrizo and Aida Shirazi\, and Jan Bevan\, poet and author.</p><p>  
 Janis Lieberman\, horn\; Matthew Vincent\, violin\; and Marc Steiner\, pi
 ano.</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p>  Program:<br />  Charles Koechlin\, Quatre Pe
 tites Pieces for Violin\, Horn and Piano<br />  Richard Aldag\, Trio for 
 Violin\, Horn and Piano<br />  Florence Price\, Fantasy No. 1 in G minor 
 for Violin and Piano<br />  Lev Kogan\, Kaddish for Horn Solo<br />  Elsa
  Barraine\, Cr├®puscules for Horn and Piano<br />  Johannes Brahms\, Trio
  in Eb Major\; Opus 40 for Piano\, Violin and Horn</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p>
   Ticket Prices:<br />  Season tickets (all 6 concerts): $155<br />  Mini
  Season (any 3 concerts): $90<br />  Individual tickets: $35<br />  Stude
 nt tickets (with valid ID): $20</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><a href="https://ww
 w.cityboxoffice.com/?category=36" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy tick
 ets here!</a></p><p>  SRJC Chamber Concerts Website: <a href="https://cha
 mberconcerts.santarosa.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://chamb
 erconcerts.santarosa.edu/</a>&#160\;</p>
