SUMMARY:DCC ASL Social Hour
DESCRIPTION:Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center for ASL Social Hours
 \, a welcoming space to practice American Sign Language (ASL)\, connect w
 ith others\, and build community in a relaxed\, supportive environment. W
 hether you're brand new to ASL or already signing\, everyone is welcome t
 o drop in\, learn\, and have fun together!  Mondays: 3:30 PM ŌĆō 4:30 PM 
  Wednesdays: 1:30 PM ŌĆō 2:30 PM  Come by\, meet new people\, and sign in
  a friendly social setting! The DCC is on the 3rd floor landing of the Be
 rtolini Student Center.  For any questions or access needs\, please email
  srjcdcc@santarosa.edu (mailto:srjcdcc@santarosa.edu)&#160\;  Visit the D
 RD website here! (https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Cente
 r for ASL Social Hours\, a welcoming space to practice American Sign Lang
 uage (ASL)\, connect with others\, and build community in a relaxed\, sup
 portive environment. Whether you're brand new to ASL or already signing\,
  everyone is welcome to drop in\, learn\, and have fun together!</p><p>  
 Mondays: 3:30 PM ŌĆō 4:30 PM<br />  Wednesdays: 1:30 PM ŌĆō 2:30 PM</p><p
 >  Come by\, meet new people\, and sign in a friendly social setting! The
  DCC is on the 3rd floor landing of the Bertolini Student Center.</p><p> 
  For any questions or access needs\, please email <a href="mailto:srjcdcc
 @santarosa.edu">srjcdcc@santarosa.edu</a>&#160\;</p><p>  Visit the <a hre
 f="https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DRD webs
