DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T123000
LOCATION:Intercultural Center\, Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:Alice Wong Memorial Event + Dim Sum Station
DESCRIPTION:Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center (DCC) and APASS for 
 a special Celebration of Life honoring Alice Wong\, a visionary Asian Ame
 rican disability rights activist whose work has shaped the Disability Vis
 ibility movement. The event will take place on March 25 from 11:00 AMŌĆō1
 2:30 PM in the SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Room 380\, and will in
 clude a livestream of the memorial happening in San Francisco with guest 
 speakers.  In addition to the livestream\, attendees are invited to gathe
 r in community with a dim sum station\, quote sharing\, and supplies to c
 ontribute to a Disability Visibility quilt being created in her honor. Al
 l students and community members are welcome to come reflect\, celebrate 
 her legacy\, and take part in this collective!Intercultural Center - Pion
 eer Hall\, Room 380\, Santa Rosa Campus  For more information\, visit: ht
 tps://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026 (https://events.sant
 arosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Cente
 r (DCC) and APASS for a special Celebration of Life honoring Alice Wong\,
  a visionary Asian American disability rights activist whose work has sha
 ped the Disability Visibility movement. The event will take place on Marc
 h 25 from 11:00 AMŌĆō12:30 PM in the SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pioneer 
 Room 380\, and will include a livestream of the memorial happening in San
  Francisco with guest speakers.</p><p>  In addition to the livestream\, a
 ttendees are invited to gather in community with a dim sum station\, quot
 e sharing\, and supplies to contribute to a Disability Visibility quilt b
 eing created in her honor. All students and community members are welcome
  to come reflect\, celebrate her legacy\, and take part in this collectiv
 e!</p><p><strong>Intercultural Center</strong> - <strong>Pioneer Hall\, R
 oom 380</strong>\, Santa Rosa Campus</p><p>  For more information\, visit
 : <a href="https://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026" target
 ="_blank" rel="noopener">https://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-mont
 h-2026</a></p>
