LOCATION:Ellis Auditorium - Petaluma Campus
SUMMARY:Sonoma County Student Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:The Sonoma County Student Film Festival was initiated 18 year
 s ago by the Student Government President\, Amanda Swan\, and launched at
  SRJC Petaluma. The Sonoma County Film Festival (SCSFF) encourages studen
 ts to build academic and professional connections with their peers and co
 mmunity. The goal of the event is to connect and introduce student filmma
 kers within the community to our own Film &amp\; Media Arts programs here
  at SRJC\, other filmmakers and film and media opportunities in the area.
   For more information\, visit the Sonoma County Student Film website! (h
 ttps://studentlife.santarosa.edu/sonoma-county-student-film-festival)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Sonoma County Student Film Festival
  was initiated 18 years ago by the Student Government President\, Amanda 
 Swan\, and launched at SRJC Petaluma. The Sonoma County Film Festival (SC
 SFF) encourages students to build academic and professional connections w
 ith their peers and community. The goal of the event is to connect and in
 troduce student filmmakers within the community to our own Film &amp\; Me
 dia Arts programs here at SRJC\, other filmmakers and film and media oppo
 rtunities in the area.</p><p>  For more information\, visit the <a href="
 https://studentlife.santarosa.edu/sonoma-county-student-film-festival" ta
 rget="_blank" rel="noopener">Sonoma County Student Film website!</a></p>
