DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T130000
LOCATION:Doyle Library\, Room 146 - Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:"Monet & Venice" Visiting Artist Lecture with Professor Heidi Saleh
DESCRIPTION:Please join Art History Professor Heidi Saleh for an upcoming
  lecture examining Claude Monet's celebrated 1908 Venetian campaign.  Des
 igned as a companion to the Monet and Venice exhibition currently on view
  (3/21/26 ŌĆō 7/26/26) at the de Young Museum in San Francisco\, this tal
 k will explore the historical and stylistic context of Monet's time in th
 e Floating City. We will analyze his approach to seriality\, his techniqu
 e for capturing light on water\, and how these canvases fit into the broa
 der trajectory of late Impressionism.  Whether you have already visited t
 he de Young exhibition or are planning a trip\, this lecture will provide
  a deeper framework for appreciating and engaging with these works.  For 
 more information\, visit SRJC's Agrella Art Gallery website! (https://art
 -gallery.santarosa.edu/exhibition/visiting-artist-lecture-series-spring-2
 026)  Also on Zoom:&#160\;https://santarosa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401 (ht
 tps://santarosa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401)&#160\;  Meeting ID: 857 4810 4
 40
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Please join Art History Professor Heidi
  Saleh for an upcoming lecture examining Claude Monet's celebrated 1908 V
 enetian campaign.</p><p>  Designed as a companion to the Monet and Venice
  exhibition currently on view (3/21/26 ŌĆō 7/26/26) at the de Young Museu
 m in San Francisco\, this talk will explore the historical and stylistic 
 context of Monet's time in the Floating City. We will analyze his approac
 h to seriality\, his technique for capturing light on water\, and how the
 se canvases fit into the broader trajectory of late Impressionism.</p><p>
   Whether you have already visited the de Young exhibition or are plannin
 g a trip\, this lecture will provide a deeper framework for appreciating 
 and engaging with these works.</p><p>  For more information\, visit <a hr
 ef="https://art-gallery.santarosa.edu/exhibition/visiting-artist-lecture-
 series-spring-2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SRJC's Agrella Art Gal
 lery website!</a></p><p>  Also on Zoom:&#160\;</p><p><a href="https://san
 tarosa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://
 santarosa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401</a>&#160\;</p><p>  Meeting ID: 857 48
 10 440</p>
